OL,3,C6.7m to cut back on showers and baths
OL,4,Cto afford rising energy bills ` survey
OL,6,FSome 6.7 million people plan to cut
OL,7,Fback on showers and baths to afford
OL,8,Frising energy costs over winter, a
OL,9,Fsurvey suggests.
OL,11,FThe poll for National Debtline found
OL,12,F45% of people are heading into the
OL,13,Fwinter period worried about their
OL,14,Ffinances, with one in four reporting
OL,15,Fthis is having a negative effect on
OL,16,Ftheir health and one in five (22%)
OL,17,Fsaying they are regularly losing sleep
OL,18,Fover money concerns.
