OL,4,Cto afford rising energy bills ` survey
OL,6,FSome 12% are planning to cut back on
OL,7,Fbaths and showers to help them afford
OL,8,Frising energy costs, the study found.
OL,10,FLatest Ofgem figures show energy
OL,11,Farrears now stand at a record #3.7
OL,12,Fbillion.
OL,14,FThe average household energy bill
OL,15,Fincreased by #149 a year from October
OL,16,F1 when the industry regulator raised
OL,17,Fits price cap to #1,717 for a typical
OL,18,Fdual fuel household in England,
OL,19,FScotland and Wales.
