OL,3,C6.7m to cut back on showers and baths
OL,4,Cto afford rising energy bills ` survey
OL,6,FNational Debtline's research found
OL,7,Fthat more than half of UK adults (53%)
OL,8,Fplan to take measures this winter to
OL,9,Fhelp afford their energy costs.
OL,11,FSome 14% plan to reduce spending at
OL,12,FChristmas, including buying fewer
OL,13,Fpresents, 14% are set to cut back on
OL,14,Fessentials such as food, toiletries
OL,15,Fand clothing, and 8% plan to sell
OL,16,Fpersonal or household items to cover
OL,17,Ftheir rising energy bills.
