OL,3,C6.7m to cut back on showers and baths
OL,4,Cto afford rising energy bills ` survey
OL,6,FSteve Vaid, chief executive of the
OL,7,FMoney Advice Trust, the charity that
OL,8,Fruns National Debtline, said: "Too
OL,9,Fmany people are heading into winter
OL,10,Fweighed down by money worries, with
OL,11,Fmillions cutting back on the very
OL,12,Fbasics, like taking fewer showers or
OL,13,Fbaths, simply to try and keep up with
OL,14,Ftheir bills.
OL,16,F"More than five million alone are
OL,17,Fregularly losing sleep, with
OL,18,Frelationships and health impacted, too.
